  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "「ネイビーブルー」では、プレイヤーは海軍艦隊を指揮し、敵の海軍力を打ち破り、彼らの本拠地を破壊することを目的としています。ゲームプレイは「バトルシップ」の一般的なルールに基づいています。プレイヤーには4×7のグリッドマップが提示され、このマップを使ってプレイヤーは…",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Navy Blue is a Strategy game, developed by Use and published by I'Max, which was released in Japan in 1992.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "Navy blue is a dark shade of the color blue. The name navy blue originally referred to the color of uniforms worn by officers in the British navy. In the late 18th century, the British Royal Navy adopted the color for its sailors' uniforms, partly due to the practical reason that dark colors were less prone to showing dirt and wear during long sea voyages. The color became so associated with naval service that it came to be known simply as \"navy blue.\"",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
  ],
